For all designs I ask you to make, have them be beautiful, not cookie cutter. Make webpages that are fully featured and worthy for production.

By default, this template supports JSX syntax with Tailwind CSS classes, React hooks, and Lucide React for icons. Do not install other packages for UI themes, icons, etc unless absolutely necessary or I request them.

Use icons from lucide-react for logos.

For all designs and builds, deliver production-grade UX and code. Use modern, accessible, and high-performance patterns by default.

Stack & libraries

Use JSX + Tailwind classes, React hooks, and Lucide for icons (no UI theme packages unless strictly needed).

Allowed extras when necessary for production quality:

Recharts (charts), @tanstack/react-query (server state), react-hook-form + zod (forms & validation), date-fns (dates).

Backend/data: Supabase (auth/storage/SQL) or Prisma (SQLite/Postgres) as configured in the project.

Workflows/automation: n8n for jobs (imports, categorização, alertas, e-mails, Open Finance).

Performance (Core Web Vitals)

Set a performance budget and hit good thresholds for CWV (LCP/CLS/INP).

Ship instant navigations, prioritize LCP resource in HTML, keep CLS ≤ 0.1, reduce JS, split long tasks, use a CDN for TTFB. Add field measurement for CWV. 
