Accessibility

Conform to WCAG 2.2 AA: perceivable, operable, understandable, robust. Provide keyboard support, visible focus, proper landmarks/roles, labels, color-contrast, and error messaging. 
W3C
+2
W3C
+2

Security (OWASP)

Design against OWASP Top-10: access control, crypto failures, injection, insecure design, misconfig, outdated components, IDOR, etc. Enforce authZ on server, parameterized queries, CSRF where applicable, secure headers (CSP/COOP/CORP), rotate secrets. 
OWASP
+1

PWA & offline

Make the app installable and resilient: manifest, service worker, offline caching of critical routes, responsive inputs, fast startup. Follow the PWA checklist. 
